<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-5854] adviceWith() just needs to start the route when the camel context is started</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5854</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An user complains the adviceWith doesn&apos;t work well with the camel-http4 component&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
After digging the code a while, I found the NPE is thrown because the camel-http4 endpoint is created before camel-http4 component is started. It is caused by the adviceWith() try to start the route after it finished the work. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to make sure the adviceWith doesn&apos;t start the route when the camel context is not started yet to avoid the NPE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/Test-Intercept-with-adviceWith-and-http-td5723473.html&lt;/p&gt;</description>
